title: Fish Trap, "Fish traps", Before 1929
creditline: Transferred from the US Department of Agriculture and Dr. E. W. Brandes, Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, E344858
description: Strips of split rattan arranged in conical formation and sewn with cross lacing or plaited strips attached to support girders at intervals of 8 centimeters. With one of these in each hand the women feel over the bottom of a creek for fish and fresh water cray fish.

tombstone.epitaph: Fish Trap, "Fish traps", Before 1929. Plaited rattan, sago-palm ribs, cane. Transferred from the US Department of Agriculture and Dr. E. W. Brandes, Department of Anthropology, National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, E344858. 15.2012.16.
